            <title>[THRIFT-3953] TSSLSocket::close should handle exceptions from waitForEvent because it is called by the destructor.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3953</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;~TSSLSocket calls TSSLSocket::close, which calls TSSLSocket::waitForEvent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TSSLSocket::waitForEvent() throws an exception in some cases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Unexpected error&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;InterruptListener has been written to&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;poll() times out&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;TSSLSocket::close should log the error but not emit an exception, similar to how it handles errors from SSL_shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13016150">THRIFT-3953</key>
